<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FC89FB72B94E" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FC89FB72B953" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,778,800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FC89FB72B953" box="[166,1225,778,800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">1. Fronto-orbital setulae only proclinate, thick, in several rows, elongated.................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FCA4FB72B94E" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,807,829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FCA4FB72B94E" box="[166,1225,807,829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">— Fronto-orbital setulae only reclinate or proclinate and reclinate together. ................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FCC7FB72B904" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FCC7FB73B929" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1224,836,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FCC7FB73B929" box="[166,1224,836,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
2. Calypter white, margin and fringe yellow; mesonotum black, shining. ............ 
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AF2FCC7FB86B92A" box="[979,1085,836,857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">rodendorfii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFEC483A2D62FCC7FB73B929" author="Spencer, K. A." box="[1091,1224,836,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" pagination="3 - 60" refId="ref5684" refString="Spencer, K. A. 1966. A revision of European species of the genera Melanagromyza Hendel and Hexomyza Enderlein, with a supplement on the genus Ophiomyia Braschnikov (Diptera: Agromyzidae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 16 (1 - 2), 3 - 60." type="journal article" year="1966">Spencer, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FCE2FB72B904" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,865,887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FCE2FB72B904" box="[166,1225,865,887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
— Calypter grey, margin and fringe black; mesonotum blackish-grey, matt. ............. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AD8FCE2FB72B904" authority="(Meigen, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1017,1225,865,887]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AD8FCE2FB8BB905" box="[1017,1072,865,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">aenea</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FCFEFB72B9C3" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FCFEFB72B9E0" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,893,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FCFEFB72B9E0" box="[166,1225,893,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
3. Frontal carina distinct, flattened (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A2B12FCFEFDCAB9E0" box="[563,625,893,915]" captionStart="Figs 19–29" captionStartId="4.[164,203,1055,1077]" captionTargetBox="[256,1132,199,1030]" captionTargetId="figure-327@4.[227,1132,174,1043]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 19–29. M. cuprea sp. n., holotype: 19, 20 — male head; 21 — phallus, ventral view; 22 — same, lateral view; 23 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 24 — ejaculatory apodeme; 25 — male wing; 26 — dorsocentral setae; paratype: 27 — spermathecae; 28 — egg guide, left blade; 29 — ventral seminal receptacle. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449446/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">fig. 19</figureCitation>
). ....................................................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FC19FB72B9C3" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,922,944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FC19FB72B9C3" box="[166,1225,922,944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
— Frontal carina absent (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A28EBFC19FDBDB9C3" box="[458,518,922,944]" captionStart="Figs 11–18" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[251,1146,992,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-369@2.[243,1147,989,1765]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 11–18. M. asymmetrica sp. n., holotype: 11, 12 — male head; 13 — phallus, ventral view; 14 — same, lateral view; 15 — epandrium-hypandrium complex and ejaculatory apodeme; 16 — male wing; paratype: 17 — spermatheca; 18 — egg guide, left blade. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">fig. 11</figureCitation>
) or crest-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A2B92FC19FD58B9C3" box="[691,739,922,944]" captionStart="Figs 1–10" captionStartId="1.[227,266,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[257,1124,172,903]" captionTargetId="figure-352@1.[248,1150,140,934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–10. M. trapezoidea sp. n., holotype: 1, 2 — male head; 3 — phallus, ventral view; 4 — same, lateral view; 5 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 6 — ejaculatory apodeme; 7 — male wing; paratype: 8 — spermathecae; 9 — egg guide, left blade; 10 — basiphallus (aberrant). Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">fig. 1</figureCitation>
). ................................................................................. 7
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FC34FB72B999" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FC34FB72B9BE" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,951,973]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FC34FB72B9BE" box="[166,1225,951,973]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">4. 3 frontal setae and 3 orbital setae, all strong on equal space from each other. .......................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FC57FB72B999" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,980,1002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FC57FB72B999" box="[166,1225,980,1002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">— 3 frontal setae and 2 orbital setae, on unequal spaces from each other. ..................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FC72FB73BE09" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FC72FB72BE33" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FC72FB72BE33" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
5. Calypter and fringe whitish-yellow, margin orange; mesonotum strongly green shining (dorsal view); 4 dorsocentral setae: two strong and 2 short and more slender (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A2A62FB8EFC38BE50" box="[835,899,1037,1059]" captionStart="Figs 19–29" captionStartId="4.[164,203,1055,1077]" captionTargetBox="[256,1132,199,1030]" captionTargetId="figure-327@4.[227,1132,174,1043]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 19–29. M. cuprea sp. n., holotype: 19, 20 — male head; 21 — phallus, ventral view; 22 — same, lateral view; 23 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 24 — ejaculatory apodeme; 25 — male wing; 26 — dorsocentral setae; paratype: 27 — spermathecae; 28 — egg guide, left blade; 29 — ventral seminal receptacle. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449446/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">fig. 26</figureCitation>
); frontal setae and orbital setae of various length (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A28A6FBA9FE57BE33" box="[391,492,1066,1088]" captionStart="Figs 19–29" captionStartId="4.[164,203,1055,1077]" captionTargetBox="[256,1132,199,1030]" captionTargetId="figure-327@4.[227,1132,174,1043]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 19–29. M. cuprea sp. n., holotype: 19, 20 — male head; 21 — phallus, ventral view; 22 — same, lateral view; 23 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 24 — ejaculatory apodeme; 25 — male wing; 26 — dorsocentral setae; paratype: 27 — spermathecae; 28 — egg guide, left blade; 29 — ventral seminal receptacle. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449446/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
). ........................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2D71FBA8FB2BBE33" authority="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit, 2016" authorityName="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit" authorityYear="2016" box="[1104,1168,1067,1088]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprea" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2D71FBA8FB2BBE33" box="[1104,1168,1067,1088]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F57DFFFEC483A2DB7FBA9FB72BE33" box="[1174,1225,1066,1088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FBC4FB73BE09" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FBC4FB73BE09" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
— Calypter and fringe whitish-grey, margin black; mesonotum black, shining (dorsal view); 2 strong dorsocentral setae; frontal setae and orbital setae equal. ................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AD0FBE7FB73BE09" authority="Spencer, 1957" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1957" box="[1009,1224,1124,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbasci">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AD0FBE7FB86BE0A" box="[1009,1085,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">verbasci</emphasis>
Spencer, 1957
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FB02FB73BF54" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FB02FB73BEA3" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FB02FB73BEA3" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
6. 2 strong dorsocentral setae, sometimes 2 short additional dorsocentral setae present; calypter and fringe dark grey, margin black; smaller species: wing length &lt;2.2 (2.1) mm, height of head &lt;0.76 (0.7) mm in male and &lt;0.87 (0.75) mm in female. .................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AFCFB39FB73BEA3" authority="Pakalniskis, 1997" authorityName="Pakalniskis" authorityYear="1997" box="[989,1224,1210,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zlobini">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AFCFB39FBA5BEBC" box="[989,1054,1210,1231]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">zlobini</emphasis>
Pakalniškis, 1997
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FB54FB73BF54" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FB54FB73BF54" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
— 1st dorsocentral setae strong and 2nd dorsocentral seta short and more slender; calypter and fringe beije, margin brown; larger species: wing length&gt; 2.2 (2.3) mm, height of head&gt; 0.77 (0.85) mm in male and&gt; 0.87 (1.0) mm in female. .................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AC2FA92FB73BF54" authority="Griffiths, 1963" authorityName="Griffiths" authorityYear="1963" box="[995,1224,1297,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="symphyti">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AC2FA92FB82BF55" box="[995,1081,1297,1318]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">symphyti</emphasis>
Griffiths, 1963
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FAAEFB72BF13" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FAAEFB72BF30" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,1325,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FAAEFB72BF30" box="[166,1225,1325,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">7. Fronto-orbital setulae reclinate and proclinate together ............................................................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FAC9FB72BF13" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" box="[166,1225,1354,1376]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FAC9FB72BF13" box="[166,1225,1354,1376]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">— Fronto-orbital setulae only reclinate. ............................................................................................................ 10</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FAE4FB72BFA0" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FAE4FB72BFE9" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FAE4FB72BFE9" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
8. 3 frontal setae, 3 orbital setae; space between all fronto-orbital bristles approximately equal; frontal carina absent (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A285CFA07FE61BFE9" box="[381,474,1412,1434]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">figs 30, 31</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2D1DFA07FB2ABFEA" authority="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit, 2016" authorityName="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit" authorityYear="2016" box="[1084,1169,1412,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2D1DFA07FB2ABFEA" box="[1084,1169,1412,1433]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F57DFFFEC483A2DB7FA07FB72BFE9" box="[1174,1225,1412,1434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FA22FB72BFA0" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FA22FB72BFA0" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">— 2 frontal setae, 2 orbital setae; space between frontal setae 2.0–2.5× as big as spaces between neighbouring 2nd frontal setae and 1st and 2nd orbital setae; frontal carina very narrow, crest-shaped. .............. 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987FA59FB72BCF3" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987FA59FB72BC59" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987FA59FB72BC59" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
9. Calypter margin yellowish, darker than calypter and fringle; mesonotum black, with bluish tinge; distiphallus triangular-shaped, elongated and narrowing posteriorly (ventral view); arms of basiphallus not connected by crosspiece (Černy, 2015: fig. 83E). ........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AE9F997FB72BC59" authority="(Fallen, 1823)" authorityName="Papp, Cerny" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[968,1225,1556,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneoventris">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AE9F997FB84BC5A" box="[968,1087,1556,1577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">aeneoventris</emphasis>
(Fallén, 1823)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987F9B2FB72BCF3" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987F9B2FB72BCF3" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
— Calypter margin white, as calypter and fringe; mesonotum black with greenish-coppery tinge; distiphallus trapezoid-shaped, widening posteriorly (ventral view); arms of basiphallus are connected by crosspiece posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A28BCF9E9FE51BCF3" box="[413,490,1642,1664]" captionStart="Figs 1–10" captionStartId="1.[227,266,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[257,1124,172,903]" captionTargetId="figure-352@1.[248,1150,140,934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–10. M. trapezoidea sp. n., holotype: 1, 2 — male head; 3 — phallus, ventral view; 4 — same, lateral view; 5 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 6 — ejaculatory apodeme; 7 — male wing; paratype: 8 — spermathecae; 9 — egg guide, left blade; 10 — basiphallus (aberrant). Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
). ................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2D03F9E9FB2ABC0C" authority="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit, 2016" authorityName="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit" authorityYear="2016" box="[1058,1169,1642,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapezoidea" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2D03F9E9FB2ABC0C" box="[1058,1169,1642,1663]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">trapezoidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F57DFFFEC483A2DB7F9E9FB72BCF3" box="[1174,1225,1642,1664]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483A2987F904FB72BCA4" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
