<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFEC483A2A0EF904FC0ABCEE" author="Guglya, Yu. A." box="[815,945,1671,1693]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref5440" refString="Guglya, Yu. A. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 15 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkiv Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (1), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A2A98F904FBBBBCEE" box="[953,1024,1671,1693]" captionStart="Figs 1–10" captionStartId="1.[227,266,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[257,1124,172,903]" captionTargetId="figure-352@1.[248,1150,140,934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–10. M. trapezoidea sp. n., holotype: 1, 2 — male head; 3 — phallus, ventral view; 4 — same, lateral view; 5 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 6 — ejaculatory apodeme; 7 — male wing; paratype: 8 — spermathecae; 9 — egg guide, left blade; 10 — basiphallus (aberrant). Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
)............................. 11
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987F927FB72BCA4" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987F927FB72BCA4" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">— Anterior margin of distiphallus flattened, concaved or slit-shaped (ventral view) (Černy, 2015: figs 91E, 95E). .................................................................................................................................................................... 12</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30FC2E13FFEC483B2987F95EFB6ABB72" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="414" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A2987F95EFB73BD5E" blockId="6.[166,1225,778,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFEC483A2987F95EFB73BD5E" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
11. Larger species: wing length&gt; 
<quantity id="4CF09B53FFEC483A2B2CF95EFDE3BC80" box="[525,600,1757,1779]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
; orbit projected above eye in profile more at level of frontal setae; lunula in centre have elongated diamond-shaped hollow; length of basiphallus 1.15× as long as width; mesophallus with parallel margins (ventral view) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFEC483A2BF3F894FCEEBD5E" author="Guglya, Yu. A." box="[722,853,1815,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref5440" refString="Guglya, Yu. A. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 15 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkiv Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (1), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEC483A2A7CF894FC35BD5E" box="[861,910,1815,1837]" captionStart="Figs 1–10" captionStartId="1.[227,266,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[257,1124,172,903]" captionTargetId="figure-352@1.[248,1150,140,934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–10. M. trapezoidea sp. n., holotype: 1, 2 — male head; 3 — phallus, ventral view; 4 — same, lateral view; 5 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 6 — ejaculatory apodeme; 7 — male wing; paratype: 8 — spermathecae; 9 — egg guide, left blade; 10 — basiphallus (aberrant). Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">fig. 2</figureCitation>
). ............ 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AC7F894FB73BD5E" authority="Hendel, 1923" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1923" box="[998,1224,1815,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AC7F894FBF8BD5F" box="[998,1091,1815,1836]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">pubescens</emphasis>
Hendel, 1923
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFED483B298FFF32FB6ABB72" blockId="7.[174,1233,177,1061]" pageId="7" pageNumber="414">
<keyLead id="30F99583FFED483B298FFF32FB6ABB72" pageId="7" pageNumber="414">
— Smaller species: wing length from &lt;
<quantity id="4CF09B53FFED483B2B77FF32FD18BAB4" box="[598,675,177,199]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
; orbit projected above eye in profile uniformly; length of basiphallus 0.72× as long as width; mesophallus strongly widening anteriorly (ventral view) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFED483B2DA5FF4DFE91BB72" author="Guglya, Yu. A." pageId="7" pageNumber="414" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref5440" refString="Guglya, Yu. A. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 15 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkiv Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (1), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFED483B2813FF68FEDBBB72" box="[306,352,235,257]" captionStart="Figs 1–10" captionStartId="1.[227,266,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[257,1124,172,903]" captionTargetId="figure-352@1.[248,1150,140,934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–10. M. trapezoidea sp. n., holotype: 1, 2 — male head; 3 — phallus, ventral view; 4 — same, lateral view; 5 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 6 — ejaculatory apodeme; 7 — male wing; paratype: 8 — spermathecae; 9 — egg guide, left blade; 10 — basiphallus (aberrant). Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449442/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="414">fig. 1</figureCitation>
). ........................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFED483B2AEAFF68FB6ABB72" authority="(de Meijere, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[971,1233,235,257]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
